OL,3,GNorthern Ireland
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FIt will be a cold start with
OL,6,Fsome frost on Friday. Then it will
OL,7,Fstay dry throughout the day with good
OL,8,Fprolonged spells of sunshine.
OL,9,
OL,10,CTonight:FStaying dry with largely
OL,11,Fclear skies at first, but high cloud
OL,12,Fgradually spreading in from the west.
OL,13,FStrong south to southwest winds
OL,14,Fdeveloping in the north and west.
OL,15,
OL,16,CSaturday:FIt will remain dry on
OL,17,FSaturday. Feeling a touch milder again
OL,18,Fwith some bright spells or hazy
OL,19,Fsunshine. Quite windy in the north and
OL,20,Fwest.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
